.75 Lime juice

node.text:
So when I get the opportunity to feature one of my all time favorite bars @thecovecocktailbar …I couldn’t wait. This bar…

I often get asked what’s one of my all time favorite bars. Yes I love craft. Yes I love lighting and beautiful interiors. The Cove is in a category all in its own. There’s an energy here that feels like something of yesteryear. I’ve spent Christmas here. They open before business work hours. I’ve met some of the most incredible single serving friends here! (Laugh at me and I’ll go Fight Club on you!)

Point being…I LOVE this bar so much. They are the best of both worlds. They are dive yet craft and In a strip mall you’d never see unless “you know.” The staff. The vibe. The amazing collection of booze.  I’ve never met the same people twice but every time I go I meet people that feel like old time friends, including the bar staff. It’s home. 

Go!  This drink is so 🔥 
Fernet / yellow chartreuse/ Demerara syrup / lemon 
#yum #cheers #westcovina

@hodordaddy of @thestatevictoriagardens making me a dealer’s choice agave cocktail.  I love the art of a “thrown” or “rolling” cocktail. The aeration releases the aromatics allowing it to develop, giving it additional depth of flavor. (I HIGHLY recommend you try an aromatic style cocktail thrown vs. stirred side by side.) 

When I went to London, I took note that almost EVERYONE used this technique. Here in the States, it’s almost non-existent.  I for one, would love to see more of it. 

 This amazing split based agave smoked drink is: 
Mezcal 
Tequila 
Dry vermouth 
Benedictine 
Grapefruit bitters
Smoketop by @middletonmixology

@hodordaddy - THANK YOU!!! 🙏 #cheers #agave
